# Configuration file for PC MORIA 5.x
#
# All lines that have the # character as the first character are
# comment lines.  Blank lines are totally ignored.



##################################################################
###                  Configuration                             ###
##################################################################

# MORIA is very easy to configure.  The biggest problem is that there
# is not enough room on a single 360K floppy disk to hold the DOS
# DOS system files, MORIA.EXE (about 340K) and a MORIA save file
# (about 80K or so).  Below are a few methods for configuring MORIA
# depending on your disk storage.  Once you decide which method to
# use, follow the instructions then remove the comment character ('#')
# from the beginning of the lines that start with 'SAVE' and 'SCORE'.
# Only remove the '#' from 1 pair of lines.



#################### 1 hard disk systems #########################
#
# Create a C:\games subdirectory on your hard disk and put C:\games
# on your PATH.  Copy MORIA.EXE and MORIA.CNF to C:\games.
#
#SAVE c:\games\moria.sav;n
#SCORE c:\games\moria.scr


#################### 2 360K floppy disk systems ##################
#
# Format /s a floppy disk and copy MORIA.CNF to it.   Format (no /s)
# a second floppy disk and copy MORIA.EXE to it.  When you want to play
# MORIA, put the first diskette in drive A, the second in drive B and
# type B:MORIA
#
#SAVE a:\moria.sav
#SCORE a:\moria.scr


#################### 1 high density floppy disk systems ##########
#
# Format /s 1 high-density diskette and copy MORIA.CNF and MORIA.EXE
# to it.
#
#SAVE a:\moria.sav
#SCORE a:\moria.scr




##################################################################
###                  Other OPTIONS                             ###
##################################################################

# These graphics characters are a solid box and a centered dot
GRAPHICS 177 249

# IBMbios option enables the numeric keypad.  Possibly unusable
# on a non-IBM clone.
IBMBIOS

# Rawio makes output somewhat faster and allows ^P (control P) to
# be used for the "previous message" MORIA command.  Cannot be
# used on a Dec Rainbow.
#RAWIO

# Being used to LARN and HACK, I prefer the ROGUE-like interface
KEYBOARD ROGUE

# It is possible to have MORIA output ANSI sequences, rather than
# use BIOS calls.  This "ANSI" option is required for Dec Rainbows
# and other computers that are not IBM BIOS compatible.
#ANSI
